p: In the last experiment, the relaxant effect of EO S in tracheal rings precontracted with ACh and preincubated with NG-nitro-L-arginine methyl ester (L-NAME) was measured. L-NAME is a very well-known endothelial NO synthase inhibitor. The concentrationâ€“response curve of EO S, compared to the control, is shown in Figure 6. The graphic shows that the relaxation was attenuated to some extent; however, EO S was still quite effective (45.41% relaxation).
